HANDOFF: Live Orb Visualizer (v1)

Objective

Build a mobile-friendly, real-time audio visualizer that:
	•	Plays an audio file
	•	Renders a particle-based orb visualizer in real time
	•	Allows live parameter adjustment with immediate feedback
	•	Supports scrubbing and playback controls
	•	Can export the visual output to MP4

This is a live visual instrument, not a video editor.

⸻

Core Principles
	•	Audio playback time is the single source of truth
	•	All visuals update in real time
	•	Parameter changes apply immediately
	•	No timeline system (no scenes, no sequencing)
	•	One evolving state only
	•	Keep UI minimal and focused
	•	Avoid unnecessary abstraction

⸻

Tech Constraints (v1)
	•	Browser-based (Canvas or WebGL acceptable, prefer Canvas 2D first)
	•	Must run on mobile browsers
	•	No heavy dependencies unless necessary
	•	Export can use:
	•	canvas frame capture + ffmpeg (or MediaRecorder if simpler)

⸻

Features (v1)

Audio
	•	Load local audio file
	•	Play / pause
	•	Scrub (seek)
	•	Loop toggle

Visualizer
	•	Particle-based orb
	•	Real-time audio-reactive motion
	•	Cohesive shape (never fully breaks apart)

