Particle System Design

Particle structure

{
  angle: number,
  radius0: number,
  x: number,
  y: number,
  vx: number,
  vy: number,
  noiseOffset: number,
  depth: number
}


⸻

Distribution (outer-mid biased)

radialBias = 0.5 + 0.5 * Math.pow(Math.random(), 0.4)
radius0 = baseRadius * radialBias


⸻

Per-frame update loop

At each frame:
	1.	Read current audio time
	2.	Compute audio features:
	•	energy (RMS)
	•	low
	•	mid
	•	high
	3.	Apply smoothing
	4.	Compute target radius
	5.	Update each particle using forces

⸻

Forces

Home attraction

ax += (homeX - x) * cohesion
ay += (homeY - y) * cohesion


⸻

Center pull

ax += -x * centerPull
ay += -y * centerPull


⸻

Radial expansion

targetRadius = baseRadius * (1 + energy * sensitivity)

dx = x / length
dy = y / length

ax += dx * (targetRadius - currentRadius) * radialStrength
ay += dy * (targetRadius - currentRadius) * radialStrength


⸻

Swirl (mid frequencies)

ax += -dy * swirl * mid
ay += dx * swirl * mid


⸻

Jitter (high frequencies)

noise = noise2D(noiseOffset + time)

ax += noise.x * jitter * high
ay += noise.y * jitter * high


⸻

Burst (low frequencies, edge-weighted)

edgeFactor = clamp(currentRadius / baseRadius, 0, 1)

burstForce = low * burst * edgeFactor

ax += dx * burstForce
ay += dy * burstForce


⸻

Damping

vx *= damping
vy *= damping


⸻

Integrate

vx += ax
vy += ay

x += vx
y += vy


⸻

Rendering

Particle appearance
	•	soft circular glints
	•	small radius
	•	additive-like blending

Color
	•	gradient based on radius

t = currentRadius / maxRadius
color = gradient(t)

Glow (simple)
	•	optional second pass
	•	larger radius, lower alpha

⸻

Audio Analysis

Use Web Audio API:
	•	Create AudioContext
	•	Use AnalyserNode
	•	Extract:
	•	time domain → RMS (energy)
	•	frequency data → bands

Band ranges:
	•	low: 20–180 Hz
	•	mid: 180–1800 Hz
	•	high: 1800–8000 Hz

